# Rust
# Cargo.lock is committed (even though this is a library) for reproducible CI:
# builds fail only on our own commits, never on a bad transitive upstream release.
# Consumers are unaffected — Cargo.lock does not propagate to downstream crates.
/target

# Environment secrets (protect all .env variants except template)
.env*
!.env.template

# IDE
.idea/
*.iml

# Private project files (not for public fork)
CLAUDE.md
docs/
.claude/
.directory
.megaignore
